notes.content: HTML is easy
Browser can execute only JavaScript
GET and POST are the most important methods of HTTP protocol
CSS is used for styling web pages
JavaScript can update and change both HTML and CSS
A JavaScript library is a collection of pre-written JavaScript
React is a popular JavaScript library for building user interfaces
Node.js allows JavaScript to be run on the server side
API stands for Application Programming Interface
JSON is a lightweight data-interchange format
REST APIs are based on the HTTP protocol
Promises in JavaScript handle asynchronous operations
AJAX allows web pages to be updated asynchronously
React components can be stateful or stateless
Redux is a state management library for JavaScript apps
HTTP status code 200 means OK
HTTP status code 404 means Not Found
HTTPS is the secure version of HTTP
Cookies are used to store data in a user's browser
LocalStorage is a web storage object available in browsers
An array is a data structure that holds multiple values
Objects in JavaScript are collections of key-value pairs
A function is a block of code designed to perform a task
Closures are functions that remember their lexical environment
A callback function is passed as an argument to another function
Arrow functions provide a shorter syntax for writing functions
The DOM stands for Document Object Model
CSS Grid is used for creating complex layouts
Flexbox is a CSS layout model for one-dimensional layouts
Media queries allow responsive design in CSS
JavaScript ES6 introduced let and const for variable declaration
Async/await syntax is used to handle asynchronous code
A module is a reusable piece of code in JavaScript
Webpack is a module bundler for JavaScript applications
Babel is a JavaScript compiler that converts ES6+ code into older JavaScript
A virtual DOM is used in libraries like React for performance
Single Page Applications load a single HTML page and update dynamically
WebSockets enable real-time communication between a client and a server
JSON Web Tokens (JWT) are used for secure data transmission
CORS stands for Cross-Origin Resource Sharing
A CDN stands for Content Delivery Network
Responsive design adapts the layout to different screen sizes
A web server serves web pages to users
A database stores and retrieves data
SQL is a language for querying databases
NoSQL databases store data in a non-relational format
MongoDB is a popular NoSQL database
A RESTful API follows REST principles
GraphQL is a query language for APIs
A frontend developer focuses on the client side of web applications
A backend developer focuses on the server side of web applications
Full-stack developers work on both the frontend and backend
DevOps practices combine development and operations
Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD) automate code deployment
A microservices architecture breaks down applications into smaller, independent services
Containers package applications with their dependencies
Docker is a popular containerization platform
Kubernetes is used for container orchestration
Serverless computing runs code without managing servers
Cloud computing provides on-demand resources over the internet
AWS, Azure, and Google Cloud are popular cloud service providers
A CDN caches content closer to users to improve performance
Version control systems like Git track changes in code
GitHub is a platform for hosting and collaborating on Git repositories
A pull request is a request to merge code changes into a repository
A branch in Git allows you to work on different versions of code simultaneously
Git merge integrates changes from different branches
A rebase in Git is an alternative to merging branches
Agile is a methodology for iterative software development
Scrum is an Agile framework for managing work
Kanban is a visual workflow management method
TDD stands for Test-Driven Development
Unit tests validate individual components of code
Integration tests verify how components work together
End-to-end tests simulate real user interactions
Jest is a popular testing framework for JavaScript
Cypress is a tool for end-to-end testing
A linting tool analyzes code for potential errors
ESLint is a linting tool for JavaScript
Prettier is a code formatter for consistent style
A CI pipeline automates testing and deployment
Continuous deployment automatically deploys code after testing
SaaS stands for Software as a Service
IaaS stands for Infrastructure as a Service
PaaS stands for Platform as a Service
Machine learning involves algorithms that improve with experience
Artificial intelligence simulates human intelligence in machines
A neural network is a type of machine learning model
Deep learning is a subset of machine learning using neural networks
Python is a popular programming language for machine learning
TensorFlow is an open-source library for machine learning
Keras is a high-level neural networks API
Data science involves extracting insights from data
Big data refers to large and complex datasets
SQL queries are used to interact with relational databases
Data visualization helps communicate data insights
D3.js is a JavaScript library for data visualization
Tableau is a powerful tool for data visualization
A heatmap is a data visualization technique
R is a programming language for statistical computing
